    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think there's a dissonance between [2930](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2930) and [2718](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2718). In 2930, I get the impression that the hash for a transaction is done by rlp-encoding into the hasher. Basically: \r\n```\r\nhash([1,[...]])\r\n```\r\nBut the 2718 spec instead sounds like the correct way to hash it would be to hash it as a prefix + opaque blob. Basically: \r\n```\r\nhash(1, [...])\r\n```\r\n (where [] means rlp-list)",
